modules.description: This module implements the Double Metaphone phonetic algorithm for string encoding. It provides functions to check vowel positions, detect Slavo-Germanic patterns, and match substrings at specific indices. It is used for generating phonetic codes that represent how words sound, particularly useful in name matching and search applications.

Implements the Soundex algorithm to convert strings into phonetic codes. Works with string inputs to produce 4-character byte sequences representing their phonetic sound. Useful for matching names that sound similar but may have different spellings, such as in record linkage or search applications.

Implements phonetic algorithms for string encoding, including DoubleMetaphone and Soundex. Provides functions to generate phonetic codes that capture how words sound, supporting name matching and search applications. Works directly with strings to produce encoded representations based on pronunciation rules.
